ent]] [[Emmanuel Macron]] for Brexit talks in [[Paris]].<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2019/0402/1040074-taoiseach_macron_meeting/  In Irish interest to protect EU single market - Varadkar] RT\u00c9 News, 2019-04-02.</ref>\n* 3 April \u2013 It was announced that turbans and the hijab would be allowed to be worn by [[Sikh]] and [[Muslim]] members of the Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/gardai-will-be-allowed-to-wear-turbans-and-the-hijab-915347.html Garda\u00ed will be allowed to wear turbans and the hijab] Irish Examiner, 2019-04-03.</ref>\n* 4 April \u2013 [[German Chancellor]] [[Angela Merkel]] met with the Taoiseach in Dublin to discuss Brexit, and show solidarity with Ireland amid the Brexit negotiations.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/merkel-shows-solidarity-with-communities-on-both-sides-of-irish-border-915567.html Merkel shows solidarity with communities on both sides of Irish border] Irish Examiner, 2019-04-04.</ref>\n* 5 April \u2013 An inquest found that a botched [[Provisional IRA|IRA]] warning call contributed to the deaths of 21 people unlawfully killed in the 1974 [[Birmingham pub bombings]].<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/botched-ira-warning-call-contributed-to-birmingham-pub-bombs-deaths-jury-finds-915701.html Botched IRA warning call contributed to Birmingham pub bombs deaths, jury finds] Irish Examiner, 2019-04-05.</ref>\n* 6 April \u2013 Irish-trained [[Tiger Roll]] won the [[2019 Grand National]], therefore becoming the tenth horse to win the race more than once.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/horse-racing/tiger-roll-earns-iconic-status-with-repeat-national-victory-37989819.html Tiger Roll earns iconic status with repeat National victory] Irish Independent, 2019-04-06.</ref>\n* 7 April \u2013 An earthquake with a magnitude of 2.4 in [[Killybegs]], [[County Donegal]] was detected by the Irish National Seismic Network.<ref>[https://www.irishexam