ependent.ie/sport/horse-racing/shock-as-michael-oleary-set-to-phase-out-gigginstown-house-stud-racing-operation-over-next-four-or-five-years-38110425.html Shock as Michael O'Leary set to phase out Gigginstown House Stud racing operation over next 'four or five years'] Irish Independent, 2019-05-14.</ref>\n* 15 May \u2013 [[United States]] sources revealed that [[US President|President]] [[Donald Trump]] would visit Ireland \"within weeks\".<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/news/us-president-donald-trump-to-visit-ireland-within-weeks-38115287.html US President Donald Trump to visit Ireland 'within weeks'] Irish Independent, 2019-05-15.</ref>\n* 16 May \u2013 Three members of an Garda S\u00edoch\u00e1na \u2013 a superintendent, an inspector and a detective \u2013 were arrested for alleged links with a Munster organised crime group.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/garda-inspector-arrested-in-relation-to-corruption-probe-released-924639.html Garda Superintendent, Inspector and Garda arrested over alleged links to organised crime in Munster] Irish Examiner, 2019-05-16.</ref>\n* 17 May \u2013 Murdered journalist [[Lyra McKee]] was posthumously honoured with a special award for outstanding commitment and contribution to journalism.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/weve-lost-a-journalist-with-very-special-qualities--lyra-mckee-honoured-with-posthumous-award-925031.html 'We\u2019ve lost a journalist with very special qualities' - Lyra McKee honoured with posthumous award] Irish Examiner, 2019-05-17.</ref>\n* 18 May \u2013 The main runway at [[Cork Airport]] was closed temporarily after a light aircraft experienced difficulties with its landing gear.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/cork-airport-runway-closed-after-aircraft-had-difficulties-with-landing-gear-925217.html Cork Airport runway closed after aircraft had 'difficulties' with landing gear] Irish Examiner, 2019-05-18.</ref>\n* 19 May \u201