ral Bank warned that a no-deal Brexit would lead to a dramatic Irish economic slowdown and result in 34,000 fewer jobs.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/34000-fewer-jobs-after-no-deal-brexit-central-bank-warns-940552.html 34,000 fewer jobs after no-deal Brexit, Central Bank warns] Irish Examiner, 2019-07-31.</ref>\n\n===August===\n* 1 August \u2013 A man whose leg got trapped on the [[Connemara]] shoreline during a rising tide was brought to safety in a multi-agency rescue.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/man-rescued-on-connemara-shoreline-after-trapping-leg-during-rising-tide-941390.html Man rescued on Connemara shoreline after trapping leg during rising tide] Irish Examiner, 2019-08-01.</ref>\n* 2 August \u2013 It was confirmed that the [[The Liffey Swim|Liffey Swim]] would go ahead as planned in spite of concerns over the result of water quality tests following a recent overflow into the river.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/update-liffey-swim-to-go-ahead-despite-significant-increase-in-bacteria-found-941567.html Update: Liffey Swim to go ahead despite significant increase in bacteria found] Irish Examiner, 2019-08-02.</ref>\n* 3 August \u2013 Taoiseach Leo Varadkar took part in [[Belfast]]'s pride parade for the first time.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2019/0803/1066773-belfast-pride-march-flag/  Taoiseach Leo Varadkar joins thousands attending Belfast pride parade] RT\u00c9 News, 2019-08-03.</ref>\n* 5 August \u2013 A 19-year-old man who was hospitalised over the weekend after taking a substance at the [[Indiependence]] music festival died.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/tributes-paid-to-teenager-who-died-after-taking-drugs-at-corks-indiependence-festival-942008.html Tributes paid to teenager who died after taking drugs at Cork's Indiependence festival] Irish Examiner, 2019-08-05.</ref>\n* 6 August \n**The number of women identified as part of the CervicalCheck IT p