7/ Former Ireland midfielder Mick Kennedy dies aged 57]</ref>\n**[[Tomi Ungerer]], 87, [[France|French]]-born author and illustrator.<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/books/tributes-paid-to-awardwinning-french-artist-and-childrens-book-author-87-who-died-in-cork-37803222.html Tributes paid to award-winning French artist and children\u2019s book author (87) who died in Cork]</ref>\n* 11 February \u2013 [[Nora Bennis]], 78, political activist and [[pro-life]] campaigner.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/ireland/tributes-paid-at-passing-of-political-activist-and-pro-life-campaigner-nora-bennis-903904.html Tributes paid at passing of political activist and pro-life campaigner, Nora Bennis]</ref>\n* 28 February \u2013 [[Noel Mulcahy]], 88, [[Fianna F\u00e1il]] politician.<ref>[https://www.limerickleader.ie/news/home/367031/influential-university-of-limerick-academic-and-former-senator-noel-mulcahy-passes-away.html Influential University of Limerick academic and former Senator Noel Mulcahy passes away]</ref>\n\n===March===\n[[File:Kevin Roche krb.00028 (cropped).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Kevin Roche]]]]\n* 1 March \u2013 [[Kevin Roche]], 96, architect, [[Pritzker Architecture Prize|Pritzker Prize]] winner (1982).<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/environment/distinguished-irish-architect-kevin-roche-dies-aged-96-1.3812597 Distinguished Irish architect Kevin Roche dies aged 96]</ref>\n* 2 March \u2013 [[Liam Gilmartin]], 97, Gaelic footballer ([[Roscommon GAA|Roscommon]]).<ref>[http://hoganstand.com/Article/Index/296281 Death of Roscommon great Liam Gilmartin]</ref>\n* 4 March \u2013 [[Edward Collins (Irish politician)|Edward Collins]], 78, politician, [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TD]] (1969\u20131987).<ref>[https://www.echolive.ie/nationalnews/Eddie-Collins-former-Fine-Gael-minister-and-TD-dies-aged-78-cb4e233d-46e7-49c4-963b-ab2d2b6ba99d-ds Eddie Collins, former Fine Gael minister and TD, dies aged 78]</ref>\n* 14 March \u2013 [[Pat Laffan]], 79, actor (''[