tes paid to late Fair City actor Tom Jordan]</ref>\n* 30 June \u2013 [[Br\u00edd\u00edn U\u00ed Mhaolag\u00e1in]], President of the [[Camogie Association]] (1991\u20131994).<ref>[http://www.camogie.ie/news.asp?id=9351 Passing of Iar-Uachtar\u00e1n Br\u00edd\u00edn U\u00ed Mhaolag\u00e1in]</ref>\n\n===July===\n[[File:Brendan Grace with Frank Sinatra.JPG|thumb|120px|[[Brendan Grace]] (left)]]\n* 1 July \u2013 Mary Coyne, 108, Ireland's oldest person.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/2019/0701/1059609-irelands-oldest-person-death/ Ireland's oldest person dies aged 108]</ref>\n* 8 July \u2013 [[Arthur Ryan]], 83, businessman, short illness.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2019/0708/1060899-arthur-ryan/ Penneys founder Arthur Ryan dies aged 83]</ref>\n* 9 July \u2013 [[John Bailey (Irish politician)|John Bailey]], 74, Fine Gael politician and [[Gaelic games]] administrator, long illness.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2019/0709/1061045-john-bailey/ FG councillor John Bailey dies]</ref>\n* 10 July \u2013 [[Noel Whelan (politician)|Noel Whelan]], 50, barrister and political analyst, short illness.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/writer-and-barrister-noel-whelan-dies-aged-50-after-short-illness-1.3953576 Noel Whelan dies aged 50 after short illness]</ref>\n* 11 July \n**[[Brendan Grace]], 68, comedian and singer, lung cancer.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2019/0711/1061410-irish-comedian-brendan-grace-has-died/ Comedian Brendan Grace has died]</ref>\n**[[S\u00e9amus Hetherton]], 89, Gaelic footballer ([[Cavan GAA|Cavan]]).<ref>[http://hoganstand.com/Article/Index/301619 Cavan 1952 All-Ireland winner passes away]</ref>\n* 14 July \u2013 [[Robert Elgie (academic)|Robert Elgie]], 54, academic.<ref>[https://www.dcu.ie/news/news/2019/Jul/DCU-President-offers-condolences-following-death-of-Professor-Robert-Elgie.shtml DCU President offers condolences following the death of Professor Robert Elgie]</ref>\n* 15 July - [[Karl Shiels]], 47, actor.<ref>[ht