news/home/437652/passing-of-tipperary-hurling-legend-john-coffey-aged-102-the-oldest-all-ireland-medal-winner.html Passing of Tipperary hurling legend John Coffey (aged 102) - the oldest All-Ireland medal winner]</ref>\n* 14 August \u2013 [[Billy Purcell]], 58, hurler ([[Fenians GAA|Fenians]], [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]]).<ref>[http://www.kilkennygaa.ie/news/read/id/2676 Billy Purcell RIP]</ref>\n* 18 August \u2013 [[Gillian Hanna]], 75, actress (''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (1998 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'', ''[[All the Queen's Men]]'', ''[[Oliver Twist (2005 film)|Oliver Twist]]''), autoimmune disease.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2019/aug/29/gillian-hanna-obituary Gillian Hanna obituary]</ref>\n\n===September===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED. Please only add people who have Wikipedia articles or whose death made national news, per [[Talk:2018 in Ireland]] -->\n* 19 September \u2013 [[Sandie Jones]], 68, singer, long illness.<ref>[https://www.rte.ie/entertainment/2019/0919/1077016-irish-eurovision-singer-sandie-jones-dies-aged-68/ Irish Eurovision singer Sandie Jones dies, aged 68]</ref>\n* 20 September \u2013 [[S\u00e9amus Hegarty]], 79, Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Raphoe|Raphoe]] (1982\u20131994) and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Derry|Derry]] (1994\u20132011).<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-49776009 Former Bishop of Derry Seamus Hegarty dies at 79]</ref>\n* 21 September \u2013 [[Gerard Mannion]], 48, theologian.<ref>[https://www.ncronline.org/news/people/noted-irish-theologian-and-ecumenist-gerard-mannion-dies-48 Noted Irish theologian and ecumenist Gerard Mannion dies at 48]</ref>\n* 25 September \u2013 [[John McAdorey]], 45, athlete, cancer.<ref>[https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/irish-olympic-sprinter-mcadorey-45-loses-cancer-battle-38535562.html Irish Olympic sprinter McAdorey (45) loses cancer battle]</ref>\n* 28 September \u2013 [[Dessie O'Halloran]], 79, singer and fiddler, short illness.<ref>[https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/musician-dessie-o-halloran-has-died-aged-79-1.4034110 Musician Dessie O\u2019Halloran has died aged 79]</ref>\n\n===October===\n<!-- PLEASE PROVIDE PROPER CITATIONS FOR ALL ITEMS ADDED. Please only add people who have Wikipedia articles or whose death made national news, per [[Talk:2018 in Ireland]] -->\n* 6 October \u2013 [[Se\u00e1n Clohessy]], 87, hurler ([[Tullaroan GAA|Tullaroan]], [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]], [[Leinster GAA|Leinster]]).<ref>[http://hoganstand.com/Article/Index/304689 Death of two-time Kilkenny All-Ireland winner Sean Clohessy]</ref>\n* 7 October \u2013 [[Ulick O'Connor]], 90, writer, historian and critic.<ref>[https://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/president-pays-tribute-after-well-loved-ulick-oconnor-dies-aged-91-955473.html President pays tribute after 'well-loved' Ulick O'Connor dies aged 91]</ref>\n* 9 October \n**[[\u00c9amonn Burns (Down Gaelic footballer)|\u00c9amonn Burns]], 56, Gaelic footballer and manager ([[Bryansford GAC|Bryansford]], [[Down GAA|Down]]).<ref>[https://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/gaelic-football/you-were-a-true-son-of-down-twotime-allireland-champion-eamonn-burns-dies-aged-55-38578772.html 'You were a true son of Down' - Two-time All-Ireland champion Eamonn Burns dies aged 55]</ref>\n**[[Thomas Flanagan (bishop)|Thomas Flanagan]], 89, Roman Catholic prelate, [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|Auxiliary Bishop Emeritus of San Antonio]] (1998-2005).<ref>[http://www.satodayscatholic.org/retired-auxiliary-bishop-thomas-flanagan-89-dies-oct-9-remembered-for-character-personal-qualities/ Retired Auxiliary Bishop Thomas Flanagan, 89, dies]</ref>\n* 28 October \u2013 [[Art Foley]], 90, hurler ([[Wexford GAA|Wexford]], [[Leinster GAA|Leinster]]).<ref>[http://hoganstand.com/Article/Index/305313 Death of legendary Wexford goalkeeper Art Foley]</ref>\n* 29 October \n**[[Pat Griffin]], 75, Gaelic footballer ([[Glenbeigh-Glencar]]