abel": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Break_Up_Song_(Little_Mix_song)"}
{"title_page": "List of CKY Crew members", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=July 2009}}\n\nThe '''Camp Kill Yourself Crew''' (referred to as '''The CKY Crew''') was a group of friends and relatives centered around [[Bam Margera]], many of whom are from or located in and around [[West Chester, Pennsylvania]]. The crew was active from  [[CKY (video series)|Landspeed presents: CKY]] (1999) to [[Minghags]] (2009). Some members of the crew were skateboarders, while others were involved either on-camera or behind-the scenes in Margera's various projects such as the [[CKY (videos)|CKY Videos]], ''[[Jackass (TV series)|Jackass]]'', ''[[Viva La Bam]]'', ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]'', ''[[Bam's Unholy Union]]'' and [[Radio Bam]].\n\nThe CKY Crew was closely linked to the band [[CKY (band)|CKY]], which features Bam's brother, Jess Margera, on drums. Music by the band was often featured in video projects members of the crew were involved with.\n\n==Main Crew==\n*[[Bam Margera]]- Professional Skateboarder for Element Skateboarding. Starred in hit movie series Jackass and his own hit reality shows Viva La Bam and Bam\u2019s Unholy Union. Known for his large weight gain in the 2010\u2019s, but has since lost a lot of weight and attempting to sober up.\n*[[Brandon DiCamillo]] \u2013 Was responsible for the Shopping Carts skit and wrote all the skits and stunts with Margera while making the CKY videos. DiCamillo was known for playing various characters in movies and in the CKY videos. He was one of the groomsmen at Margera's wedding. After 2009's ''Minghags'', DiCamillo has not appeared in any CKY related project. It is believed he decided to move out of the public eye. This was confirmed by [[Joe Frantz]] in 2017<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gvK4yOWsmGQ&t=912s</ref>, stating that DiCamillo formally renounced his affiliation with the CKY crew years prior.\n*[[Ryan Dunn]] \u2013 Dunn was part of both the CKY and Jackass crews. He and Margera participated in the [[Gumball 3000]] three times in the years 2005, 2006 and 2008. Dunn also starred in Margera's directorial debut, ''Haggard: The Movie''. Dunn died in a drunk-driving incident on June 20, 2011.[2]\n*[[Chris Raab]] (aka Raab Himself) \u2013 Appeared in all of the CKY videos. Raab left the crew shortly after the filming of ''Viva La Bam'' in 2006 after having a dispute with Margera for unknown reasons. This was later cleared up by Raab, stating the reason he left was to live a more sober lifestyle.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vUUDVAHXHVg&t=3910s</ref> He released his movie ''Hotdog Casserole'' in 2008. Raab made his most recent appearance in MTV's \"A Tribute to Ryan Dunn\" alongside Margera in 2011.\n*[[Rake Yohn]] (real name Edward Webb) \u2013 Known for his long hair, love for metal, and strong dislike of mustard. He is also a chemist after receiving his BS at Penn State. Alongside DiCamillo, he co-hosted the show ''Blastazoid''. They also both appear in Raab's movie ''Hotdog Casserole''.\n\n==The Margeras==\n*[[April Margera]] \u2013 Bam's mother\n*[[Phil Margera]] \u2013 Bam's father\n*[[Boof Margera]] \u2013 Bam's step aunt\n*[[Vincent Margera]] \u2013 a.k.a. \"Don Vito\". Bam's uncle. He died of liver and kidney failure on November 15, 2015.\n*[[Jess Margera]] \u2013 Bam's brother. He plays drums for [[CKY (band)|CKY]], [[Gnarkill]], [[Viking Skull]], and [[The Company Band]]. Jess was Bam's [[groomsman|best man]] at his wedding.\n*'''Darlene Margera''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Mum-Mum\" or \"Mom-Mom\". She is Phil and Vincent's mother, April's mother-in-law and the grandmother of Jess and Bam Margera. She made a few appearances on Viva La Bam, Bam's Unholy Union and in the CKY Videos. She died in 2007.\n*'''Phillip \"Pop-Pop\" Margera Sr.'''<ref>Confirmed first name on the Minghags website</ref> \u2013 The father of Phil Margera and Don Vito. Appeared in Viva La Bam, Bam's Unholy Union, ''Haggard: The Movie'' and ''Minghags: The Movie''. He is credited for giving Brandon Margera the \"Bam\" nickname.\n\n==Others==\n*'''Dave Battaro''' \u2013 a.k.a. Lord Battaro. He and DiCamillo roomed together before. He played the \"Mustard Man\" in CKY4.\n*'''Matt Cole''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Shitbird\". Bam's uncle on April's side. Plays guitar for [[Gnarkill]]. Has appeared in [[Bam's Unholy Union]]. Is on [[Radio Bam]] regularly. He was one of the groomsmen in Bam's wedding. He also appeared in \"Where The #$&% is Santa?\", and briefly toured with [[CKY (band)|CKY]] as a keyboardist.\n*'''Dave Decurtis''' \u2013 a.k.a. Naked Dave. He appears in Margera's works naked (hence the nickname). A stunt of him running naked in front of a van was featured on [[Jackass (TV Show)|Jackass]] and originally appeared on CKY. He usually has clothes on only when not filiming, he is often compared to Nudie Novak.\n*'''[[Jason Ellis (radio host)|Jason Ellis]]''' \u2013 Pro-skater. He has appeared in [[Viva La Bam]] and ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]''. He had a show on [[SpikeTV]] called The Wild World of Spike, currently the host of the Jason Ellis Show.\n*'''[[Joe Frantz]]''' \u2013 Under Bam's direction, [[Joe Frantz]] has served multiple roles as Producer and Director Of Photography on the independent films [[Haggard: The Movie|Haggard]] and [[Minghags]], the [[CKY (video series)|CKY]] Video Series (CKY3 and CKY4), and music videos for [[HIM (Finnish band)|HIM]], [[CKY (band)|CKY]], [[The 69 Eyes]] (as well as other popular bands).  Frantz is also one of the cameramen behind [[Jackass 2]], [[Jackass 2.5]], and [[Jackass 3D]]. He was also in the show [[Blastazoid]] with Rake Yohn and Brandon DiCamillo. Frantz is known for the on-screen appearances he has made in the works he produces, in television shows and films such as [[MTV]]'s [[Viva La Bam]], [[Bam's Unholy Union]], the CKY Video Series, and [[Bam Margera Presents: Where the#$&% Is Santa?]]. He also is a collaborative coauthor of the book [[Dreamseller]], which he wrote with [[MTV]]/Jackass personality [[Brandon Novak]].\n*'''Ryan Gee''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Shitgoose\", \"The Gill\". He is a professional photographer who works with Bam on many of his projects including the behind-the-scenes footage for \"Minghags\".\n*[[Kerry Getz]] \u2013 Pro-skater known for his tantrums while skateboarding, which is why on the first CKY video he is nicknamed ' Hockey Temper'.\n*[[Chad I. Ginsburg]]- CKY's guitarist. He was one of the groomsmen at Bam's wedding. Operates the soundboard on [[Radio Bam]]. He also appeared in Bam's Unholy Union and Where the #$&% is Santa.  \n*'''Chris and Mark Hanna''' \u2013 Brothers. Chris is involved with Bam's work and managed [[CKY (band)|CKY]] on the Viva La Bands tour. They both used to be neighbors with the Margera's. Mark was good friends with Bam and appears in CKY 3, the CKY Documentary, Haggard: The Movie, Viva La Bam, Minghags and Where the #$&% is Santa. Mark has also been a drum tech for CKY on various tours.\n*[[Tony Hawk]] \u2013 a.k.a. Birdman. Professional skateboarding legend. Has made several appearances on Viva La Bam.  \n*[[Terry Kennedy (skateboarder)|Terry Kennedy]] \u2013 a.k.a. Compton Ass Terry. Professional skateboarder. He appeared on Viva La Bam and appeared in  Minghags.\n*'''Mike Maldonado''' -Professional skater who has appeared in the CKY videos.\n*[[Deron Miller]] \u2013 Ex CKY singer / guitarist. Has appeared off and on in Bam's projects. He is married to [[Felissa Rose]], star of the horror movie [[Sleepaway Camp]], which CKY used a screenshot from for the album artwork of their Disengage The Simulator EP and other merchandise. They have three children together.\n*'''Tim Glomb''' \u2013 A skilled carpenter and construction worker with a knack for skateboard park building. He made several appearances in the first few seasons of Viva la Bam and towards the end had become a regular. During Viva la Bam in the first episode he built skateboarding ramps all over the interior and exterior of Bam's house. He is credited on \"Where The #$&% is Santa\" for helping with the story. He now splits his time between [[Denver]], [[Colorado]] and Pennsylvania.\n*[[Brandon Novak]] \u2013 Former pro-skater & Bam's childhood friend. Appeared in Haggard as a drug dealer while battling his own addictions. The documentary for Haggard ended up being about him and Ryan Dunn confronting him about it. He was a regular on Bam's Unholy Union and was one of Bam's Grooms men. He has small roles in Bam's other projects as well including Jackass and Minghags.  \n*'''Tim O'Connor''' \u2013 He has appeared in many episodes of Viva La Bam. He has also appeared in the CKY videos. Tim was a MADE coach on MTV's ''[[Made (TV series)|Made]].\n*[[Mike Vallely]] \u2013 Professional skateboarder. He appeared in a several CKY movies and Viva La Bam episodes.\n*'''Art Webb''' \u2013 Rake Yohn's brother. He is credited as \"Art Webb 1986\" because of his love for music in that particular year. Art's longest known speaking part comes in an unscripted tirade in the documentary in the ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]'' bonus features when he professes his willingness to act as [[Tony Hawk]]'s bodyguard. He now runs a podcast called \"Gamecasa\". Art also played a speaking role in the video game \"Trials 2\" along with Brandon and Rake.\n*[[CKY (band)|Vernon Zaborowski]]- Former Bass Player for CKY.  He was featured briefly in the  [[CKY (video series)|CKY]] video series. Vern briefly reunited with the band to perform one song at the [[San Jose, California|San Jose]] stop of [[Warped Tour 2017]].\n\n== Reunions ==\n\nIn 2011, a few members of the crew briefly reunited for [[MTV]]'s Tribute to the late [[Ryan Dunn]].  [[Bam Margera]], [[Jess Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]] and [[Chris Raab]] were all featured in the special.\n\nOn November 2, 2014, [[MTV]] aired a special called ''CKY: The Greatest Hits''. It featured new interviews with [[Bam Margera]], [[Jess Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]], [[April Margera]], [[Phil Margera]], Dave Battaro and [[Joe Frantz]]. With special appearances from [[Johnny Knoxville]], [[Jeff Tremaine]], [[Kerry Getz]] and Tim O'Connor. The special also featured unreleased footage documenting the series as a whole. The special was directed by longtime CKY Crew member and cinematographer [[Joe Frantz]].<ref>http://www.mtv.com/videos/misc/1094793/cky-the-greatest-hits-sneak-peek.jhtml</ref>\n\nIn 2018, [[Chris Raab]] featured many of the crew members on his \"Bathroom Break\" Podcast. Guests so far include: [[Brandon Novak]], [[Joe Frantz]], [[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Deron Miller]], [[Jess Margera]], Dave Battaro and [[CKY (band)|Vernon Zaborowski]]. <ref>https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAN9l6TnORmVZZBFdIy9Qiw</ref> Dicamillo reportedly declined to appear.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZrqG0RH5CWs&t=2838s</ref>\n\n==CKY Crew Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Film\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Main Members Involved \n|-\n|1999\n|''[[CKY (video series)|Landspeed presents: CKY]]''\n|rowspan=7|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Chris Raab]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY2K|CKY2K]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2001\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY 3|CKY3]]''\n|-\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY Documentary|CKY Documentary]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2002\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY4: The Latest & Greatest|CKY4: The Latest & Greatest]]''\n|-\n|''[[Jackass: The Movie]]''\n\n|-\n|''[[Haggard: The Movie]]''\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[Jackass Number Two]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]] (Cameo), [[Rake Yohn]] (Cameo)\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Jackass 2.5]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Minghags: The Movie]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Jackass 3D]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]],  [[Rake Yohn]] (Cameo)\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Jackass 3.5]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Main Members Involved\n|-\n|2000\u20132002\n|''[[Jackass (TV series)|Jackass]]''\n|rowspan=2|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Chris Raab]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2003\u20132006\n|''[[Viva La Bam]]''\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Bam's Unholy Union]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Bam's World Domination]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]]\n|-\n|2011\n|''A Tribute to Ryan Dunn''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]]\n|-\n|2014\n|''CKY: The Greatest Hits''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{CKY}}   \n{{jackass}}\nhttp://www.dickhouse.tv\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Cky Crew Members}}\n[[Category:CKY]]\n[[Category:Pranksters]]\n\n[[pl:Ekipa CKY]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=July 2009}}\n\nThe '''Camp Kill Yourself Crew''' (referred to as '''The CKY Crew''') was a group of friends and relatives centered around [[Bam Margera]], many of whom are from or located in and around [[West Chester, Pennsylvania]]. The crew was active from  [[CKY (video series)|Landspeed presents: CKY]] (1999) to [[Minghags]] (2009). Some members of the crew were skateboarders, while others were involved either on-camera or behind-the scenes in Margera's various projects such as the [[CKY (videos)|CKY Videos]], ''[[Jackass (TV series)|Jackass]]'', ''[[Viva La Bam]]'', ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]'', ''[[Bam's Unholy Union]]'' and [[Radio Bam]].\n\nThe CKY Crew was closely linked to the band [[CKY (band)|CKY]], which features Bam's brother, Jess Margera, on drums. Music by the band was often featured in video projects members of the crew were involved with.\n\n==Main Crew==\n*[[Bam Margera]]- Professional Skateboarder for Element Skateboarding. Starred in hit movie series Jackass and his own hit reality shows Viva La Bam and Bam\u2019s Unholy Union. Known for hi large weight gain in the 2010\u2019s, but has since lost a lot of weight and attempting to sober up.\n*[[Brandon DiCamillo]] \u2013 Was responsible for the Shopping Carts skit and wrote all the skits and stunts with Margera while making the CKY videos. DiCamillo was known for playing various characters in movies and in the CKY videos. He was one of the groomsmen at Margera's wedding. After 2009's ''Minghags'', DiCamillo has not appeared in any CKY related project. It is believed he decided to move out of the public eye. This was confirmed by [[Joe Frantz]] in 2017<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gvK4yOWsmGQ&t=912s</ref>, stating that DiCamillo formally renounced his affiliation with the CKY crew years prior.\n*[[Ryan Dunn]] \u2013 Dunn was part of both the CKY and Jackass crews. He and Margera participated in the [[Gumball 3000]] three times in the years 2005, 2006 and 2008. Dunn also starred in Margera's directorial debut, ''Haggard: The Movie''. Dunn died in a drunk-driving incident on June 20, 2011.[2]\n*[[Chris Raab]] (aka Raab Himself) \u2013 Appeared in all of the CKY videos. Raab left the crew shortly after the filming of ''Viva La Bam'' in 2006 after having a dispute with Margera for unknown reasons. This was later cleared up by Raab, stating the reason he left was to live a more sober lifestyle.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vUUDVAHXHVg&t=3910s</ref> He released his movie ''Hotdog Casserole'' in 2008. Raab made his most recent appearance in MTV's \"A Tribute to Ryan Dunn\" alongside Margera in 2011.\n*[[Rake Yohn]] (real name Edward Webb) \u2013 Known for his long hair, love for metal, and strong dislike of mustard. He is also a chemist after receiving his BS at Penn State. Alongside DiCamillo, he co-hosted the show ''Blastazoid''. They also both appear in Raab's movie ''Hotdog Casserole''.\n\n==The Margeras==\n*[[April Margera]] \u2013 Bam's mother\n*[[Phil Margera]] \u2013 Bam's father\n*[[Boof Margera]] \u2013 Bam's step aunt\n*[[Vincent Margera]] \u2013 a.k.a. \"Don Vito\". Bam's uncle. He died of liver and kidney failure on November 15, 2015.\n*[[Jess Margera]] \u2013 Bam's brother. He plays drums for [[CKY (band)|CKY]], [[Gnarkill]], [[Viking Skull]], and [[The Company Band]]. Jess was Bam's [[groomsman|best man]] at his wedding.\n*'''Darlene Margera''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Mum-Mum\" or \"Mom-Mom\". She is Phil and Vincent's mother, April's mother-in-law and the grandmother of Jess and Bam Margera. She made a few appearances on Viva La Bam, Bam's Unholy Union and in the CKY Videos. She died in 2007.\n*'''Phillip \"Pop-Pop\" Margera Sr.'''<ref>Confirmed first name on the Minghags website</ref> \u2013 The father of Phil Margera and Don Vito. Appeared in Viva La Bam, Bam's Unholy Union, ''Haggard: The Movie'' and ''Minghags: The Movie''. He is credited for giving Brandon Margera the \"Bam\" nickname.\n\n==Others==\n*'''Dave Battaro''' \u2013 a.k.a. Lord Battaro. He and DiCamillo roomed together before. He played the \"Mustard Man\" in CKY4.\n*'''Matt Cole''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Shitbird\". Bam's uncle on April's side. Plays guitar for [[Gnarkill]]. Has appeared in [[Bam's Unholy Union]]. Is on [[Radio Bam]] regularly. He was one of the groomsmen in Bam's wedding. He also appeared in \"Where The #$&% is Santa?\", and briefly toured with [[CKY (band)|CKY]] as a keyboardist.\n*'''Dave Decurtis''' \u2013 a.k.a. Naked Dave. He appears in Margera's works naked (hence the nickname). A stunt of him running naked in front of a van was featured on [[Jackass (TV Show)|Jackass]] and originally appeared on CKY. He usually has clothes on only when not filiming, he is often compared to Nudie Novak.\n*'''[[Jason Ellis (radio host)|Jason Ellis]]''' \u2013 Pro-skater. He has appeared in [[Viva La Bam]] and ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]''. He had a show on [[SpikeTV]] called The Wild World of Spike, currently the host of the Jason Ellis Show.\n*'''[[Joe Frantz]]''' \u2013 Under Bam's direction, [[Joe Frantz]] has served multiple roles as Producer and Director Of Photography on the independent films [[Haggard: The Movie|Haggard]] and [[Minghags]], the [[CKY (video series)|CKY]] Video Series (CKY3 and CKY4), and music videos for [[HIM (Finnish band)|HIM]], [[CKY (band)|CKY]], [[The 69 Eyes]] (as well as other popular bands).  Frantz is also one of the cameramen behind [[Jackass 2]], [[Jackass 2.5]], and [[Jackass 3D]]. He was also in the show [[Blastazoid]] with Rake Yohn and Brandon DiCamillo. Frantz is known for the on-screen appearances he has made in the works he produces, in television shows and films such as [[MTV]]'s [[Viva La Bam]], [[Bam's Unholy Union]], the CKY Video Series, and [[Bam Margera Presents: Where the#$&% Is Santa?]]. He also is a collaborative coauthor of the book [[Dreamseller]], which he wrote with [[MTV]]/Jackass personality [[Brandon Novak]].\n*'''Ryan Gee''' \u2013 a.k.a. \"Shitgoose\", \"The Gill\". He is a professional photographer who works with Bam on many of his projects including the behind-the-scenes footage for \"Minghags\".\n*[[Kerry Getz]] \u2013 Pro-skater known for his tantrums while skateboarding, which is why on the first CKY video he is nicknamed ' Hockey Temper'.\n*[[Chad I. Ginsburg]]- CKY's guitarist. He was one of the groomsmen at Bam's wedding. Operates the soundboard on [[Radio Bam]]. He also appeared in Bam's Unholy Union and Where the #$&% is Santa.  \n*'''Chris and Mark Hanna''' \u2013 Brothers. Chris is involved with Bam's work and managed [[CKY (band)|CKY]] on the Viva La Bands tour. They both used to be neighbors with the Margera's. Mark was good friends with Bam and appears in CKY 3, the CKY Documentary, Haggard: The Movie, Viva La Bam, Minghags and Where the #$&% is Santa. Mark has also been a drum tech for CKY on various tours.\n*[[Tony Hawk]] \u2013 a.k.a. Birdman. Professional skateboarding legend. Has made several appearances on Viva La Bam.  \n*[[Terry Kennedy (skateboarder)|Terry Kennedy]] \u2013 a.k.a. Compton Ass Terry. Professional skateboarder. He appeared on Viva La Bam and appeared in  Minghags.\n*'''Mike Maldonado''' -Professional skater who has appeared in the CKY videos.\n*[[Deron Miller]] \u2013 Ex CKY singer / guitarist. Has appeared off and on in Bam's projects. He is married to [[Felissa Rose]], star of the horror movie [[Sleepaway Camp]], which CKY used a screenshot from for the album artwork of their Disengage The Simulator EP and other merchandise. They have three children together.\n*'''Tim Glomb''' \u2013 A skilled carpenter and construction worker with a knack for skateboard park building. He made several appearances in the first few seasons of Viva la Bam and towards the end had become a regular. During Viva la Bam in the first episode he built skateboarding ramps all over the interior and exterior of Bam's house. He is credited on \"Where The #$&% is Santa\" for helping with the story. He now splits his time between [[Denver]], [[Colorado]] and Pennsylvania.\n*[[Brandon Novak]] \u2013 Former pro-skater & Bam's childhood friend. Appeared in Haggard as a drug dealer while battling his own addictions. The documentary for Haggard ended up being about him and Ryan Dunn confronting him about it. He was a regular on Bam's Unholy Union and was one of Bam's Grooms men. He has small roles in Bam's other projects as well including Jackass and Minghags.  \n*'''Tim O'Connor''' \u2013 He has appeared in many episodes of Viva La Bam. He has also appeared in the CKY videos. Tim was a MADE coach on MTV's ''[[Made (TV series)|Made]].\n*[[Mike Vallely]] \u2013 Professional skateboarder. He appeared in a several CKY movies and Viva La Bam episodes.\n*'''Art Webb''' \u2013 Rake Yohn's brother. He is credited as \"Art Webb 1986\" because of his love for music in that particular year. Art's longest known speaking part comes in an unscripted tirade in the documentary in the ''[[Haggard: The Movie]]'' bonus features when he professes his willingness to act as [[Tony Hawk]]'s bodyguard. He now runs a podcast called \"Gamecasa\". Art also played a speaking role in the video game \"Trials 2\" along with Brandon and Rake.\n*[[CKY (band)|Vernon Zaborowski]]- Former Bass Player for CKY.  He was featured briefly in the  [[CKY (video series)|CKY]] video series. Vern briefly reunited with the band to perform one song at the [[San Jose, California|San Jose]] stop of [[Warped Tour 2017]].\n\n== Reunions ==\n\nIn 2011, a few members of the crew briefly reunited for [[MTV]]'s Tribute to the late [[Ryan Dunn]].  [[Bam Margera]], [[Jess Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]] and [[Chris Raab]] were all featured in the special.\n\nOn November 2, 2014, [[MTV]] aired a special called ''CKY: The Greatest Hits''. It featured new interviews with [[Bam Margera]], [[Jess Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]], [[April Margera]], [[Phil Margera]], Dave Battaro and [[Joe Frantz]]. With special appearances from [[Johnny Knoxville]], [[Jeff Tremaine]], [[Kerry Getz]] and Tim O'Connor. The special also featured unreleased footage documenting the series as a whole. The special was directed by longtime CKY Crew member and cinematographer [[Joe Frantz]].<ref>http://www.mtv.com/videos/misc/1094793/cky-the-greatest-hits-sneak-peek.jhtml</ref>\n\nIn 2018, [[Chris Raab]] featured many of the crew members on his \"Bathroom Break\" Podcast. Guests so far include: [[Brandon Novak]], [[Joe Frantz]], [[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Deron Miller]], [[Jess Margera]], Dave Battaro and [[CKY (band)|Vernon Zaborowski]]. <ref>https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAN9l6TnORmVZZBFdIy9Qiw</ref> Dicamillo reportedly declined to appear.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZrqG0RH5CWs&t=2838s</ref>\n\n==CKY Crew Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Film\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Main Members Involved \n|-\n|1999\n|''[[CKY (video series)|Landspeed presents: CKY]]''\n|rowspan=7|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Chris Raab]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY2K|CKY2K]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2001\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY 3|CKY3]]''\n|-\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY Documentary|CKY Documentary]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2002\n|''[[CKY (video series)#CKY4: The Latest & Greatest|CKY4: The Latest & Greatest]]''\n|-\n|''[[Jackass: The Movie]]''\n\n|-\n|''[[Haggard: The Movie]]''\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[Jackass Number Two]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]] (Cameo), [[Rake Yohn]] (Cameo)\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Jackass 2.5]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Minghags: The Movie]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Jackass 3D]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]],  [[Rake Yohn]] (Cameo)\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Jackass 3.5]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Main Members Involved\n|-\n|2000\u20132002\n|''[[Jackass (TV series)|Jackass]]''\n|rowspan=2|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Chris Raab]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2003\u20132006\n|''[[Viva La Bam]]''\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Bam's Unholy Union]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Brandon Dicamillo]], [[Rake Yohn]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Bam's World Domination]]''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Ryan Dunn]]\n|-\n|2011\n|''A Tribute to Ryan Dunn''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]]\n|-\n|2014\n|''CKY: The Greatest Hits''\n|[[Bam Margera]], [[Rake Yohn]], [[Chris Raab]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{CKY}}   \n{{jackass}}\nhttp://www.dickhouse.tv\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Cky Crew Members}}\n[[Category:CKY]]\n[[Category:Pranksters]]\n\n[[pl:Ekipa CKY]]\n", "name_user": "HynesTighe", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMain Crew", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_CKY_Crew_members"}
{"title_page": "Zbigniew Stonoga", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Zbigniew Stonoga\n| image              = Zbigniew Stonoga.jpg\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1974|10|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ozimek]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[Poland|Polish]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = entrepreneur, philanthropist, whistleblower, activist\n| years_active       = 1999-present\n| known_for          = Political activism, whistleblowing, philanthropy, videoblogging\n| notable_works      = \n| party              = [[Congress of the New Right|KNP]] <small>(2014)</small><br />[[Stonoga Partia Polska|SPP]] <small>(2015)</small>\n| opponents          = Law and Justice, Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski\n| criminal_charge    = Fraud\n| website            = \n}}\n'''Zbigniew Stonoga''' ({{IPA-pl|\u02c8zbi\u0261\u0272\u025bf st\u0254\u02c8n\u0254\u0261a|pron}}; born 17 October 1974 in [[Ozimek]])<ref name=\"dziennik1\">{{cite news|title=Ju\u017c si\u0119 powyg\u0142upia\u0142em, pokl\u0105\u0142em. Tak wojuje Zbigniew Stonoga. SYLWETKA |url = http://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/wydarzenia/artykuly/475076,zbigniew-stonoga-kontra-sokolowski-i-sld-wojny-zbigniewa-stonogi.html |accessdate = 18 June 2015| date = 9 June 2015}}</ref> is a Polish entrepreneur, businessman, activist and philanthropist who gained notoriety as a [[whistleblower]] for the publication of the investigation files concerning the [[Wprost#Role in the 2014 government bugging scandal|Polish bugging scandal (2014\u20132015)]], known as Waitergate, and for anti-government activity. Founder of the short-lived [[Stonoga Party Poland]] (also known in English as The Centipede Party, since ''Stonoga'' translates as \"centipede\").<ref>{{cite news| url = http://telewizjarepublika.pl/stonoga-partia-polska-rejestracja-nowej-formacji-politycznej-moze-nastapic-lada-dzien,20590.htm| title = \"Stonoga Partia Polska. Rejestracja nowej formacji politycznej mo\u017ce nast\u0105pi\u0107 lada dzie\u0144\". | date = 10 June 2015 | accessdate  = 18 June 2015 }}</ref> Founder of ''Gazeta Stonoga'' (now defunct). Convicted for financial fraud.\n\n==Biography ==\n\n=== Academic background ===\nAfter graduating from an electrotechnical college, he started higher education which he did not complete. Claims to have studied law at the [[University of Warsaw]]; however, the University denies such person has ever attended the university.<ref name=\"dziennik1\"/>\n\n=== Political career ===\nIn 2015 he ran in Polish parliamentary elections in which his party, Stonoga Party Poland, scored 0.4% (40 000 voters). After the results were announced, furious Stonoga uploaded a video to the internet in which he expressed his frustration with those who did not vote for him or for the [[Coalition for the Renewal of the Republic - Liberty and Hope]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qARYM_ACOk|title=Zbigniew Stonoga obra\u017ca Polak\u00f3w: \"WAS POLACZKI TYLKO DO AUSCHWITZ WYPROWADZI\u0106\"|date=2015-08-31|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=2017-04-20}}</ref>\n\nHis language is vulgar and direct, attracting the attention of young audiences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kontrrewolucja.net/wiadomosci/stonoga-szokuje-wulgarnie-wyzywa-politykow-tym-prezydenta|title=Stonoga znowu szokuje. Wulgarnie wyzywa polityk\u00f3w, w tym prezydenta (WIDEO)|date=2017-04-06|website=Kontrrewolucja.net|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pch24.pl/glupie-polaczki--was-tylko-do-auschwitz-zaprowadzac---sfrustrowany-stonoga-o-porazce-wyborczej--w-kolejnym-nagraniu-przeprosil-za-slowa,39007,i.html|title=\"G\u0142upie polaczki, was tylko do Auschwitz zaprowadza\u0107\" \u2013 sfrustrowany Stonoga o pora\u017cce wyborczej. W kolejnym nagraniu przeprosi\u0142 za s\u0142owa|website=Pch24.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n==  Lawsuits ==\nIn the 2000s Stonoga was named in a total of 89 criminal lawsuits.\n\nIn 2004 he was sentenced to 3.5 years' imprisonment for financial irregularities. In 2005 his sentence was quashed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ju\u017c si\u0119 powyg\u0142upia\u0142em, pokl\u0105\u0142em. Tak wojuje Zbigniew Stonoga. SYLWETKA |url = http://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/wydarzenia/artykuly/475076,zbigniew-stonoga-kontra-sokolowski-i-sld-wojny-zbigniewa-stonogi.html |language=pl| accessdate = 18 June 2015| date = 9 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nBy 2015, he was named in 61 criminal cases related mostly to financial fraud and insulting public servants; he was sentenced to a year in prison for fraud on a private car sale.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.polityka.pl/tygodnikpolityka/kraj/1623573,1,stonoga-raczej-do-wiezienia-niz-do-sejmu.read | title = Stonoga raczej do wi\u0119zienia ni\u017c do Sejmu | language=pl}}</ref>\n\nOn May 9, 2017, Stonoga was imprisoned at the Warszawa-Bialoleka correctional center for one year on charges of committing a large-scale financial fraud; the sentence was later shortened by 3 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wprost.pl/kraj/10053826/zbigniew-stonoga-trafil-do-wiezienia-spedzi-tam-niecaly-rok.html|title=Zbigniew Stonoga trafi\u0142 do wi\u0119zienia. Sp\u0119dzi tam nieca\u0142y rok|date=2017-05-09|website=Wprost|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.wp.pl/zbigniew-stonoga-za-kratkami-spedzi-tam-dluzszy-czas-6120729443526785a|title=Zbigniew Stonoga za kratkami. Sp\u0119dzi tam d\u0142u\u017cszy czas|last=K\u0142oszewski|first=oprac Jakub|date=2017-05-09|website=wiadomosci.wp.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dziennikzachodni.pl/zbigniew-stonoga-wyszedl-z-wiezienia-i-prosi-o-wplate-200-tys-zl-na-wolnosci-opublikowal-wideo-27-9-2019/ar/c1-14433723|title=Zbigniew Stonoga wyszed\u0142 z wi\u0119zienia i prosi o wp\u0142at\u0119 200 tys. z\u0142. Na wolno\u015bci opublikowa\u0142 wideo [27. 9. 2019]|last=Redakcja|date=2019-09-27|website=Dziennik Zachodni|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Wikiquote|Zbigniew Stonoga}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stonoga, Zbigniew}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Polish businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Polish activists]]\n[[Category:Polish politicians]]\n[[Category:Polish YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Whistleblowers]]\n[[Category:Men whistleblowers]]\n\n\n{{Poland-business-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Zbigniew Stonoga\n| image              = Zbigniew Stonoga.jpg\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1974|10|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ozimek]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = [[Poland|Polish]]\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = entrepreneur, philanthropist, whistleblower, activist\n| years_active       = 1999-present\n| known_for          = Political activism, whistleblowing, philanthropy, videoblogging\n| notable_works      = \n| party              = [[Congress of the New Right|KNP]] <small>(2014)</small><br />[[Stonoga Partia Polska|SPP]] <small>(2015)</small>\n| opponents          = Law and Justice, Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski\n| criminal_charge    = Fraud\n| website            = \n}}\n'''Zbigniew Stonoga''' ({{IPA-pl|\u02c8zbi\u0261\u0272\u025bf st\u0254\u02c8n\u0254\u0261a|pron}}; born 17 October 1974 in [[Ozimek]])<ref name=\"dziennik1\">{{cite news|title=Ju\u017c si\u0119 powyg\u0142upia\u0142em, pokl\u0105\u0142em. Tak wojuje Zbigniew Stonoga. SYLWETKA |url = http://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/wydarzenia/artykuly/475076,zbigniew-stonoga-kontra-sokolowski-i-sld-wojny-zbigniewa-stonogi.html |accessdate = 18 June 2015| date = 9 June 2015}}</ref> is a Polish entrepreneur, businessman, activist and philanthropist who gained notoriety as a [[whistleblower]] for the publication of the investigation files concerning the [[Wprost#Role in the 2014 government bugging scandal|Polish bugging scandal (2014\u20132015)]], known as Waitergate, and for anti-government activity. Founder of the short-lived [[Stonoga Party Poland]] (also known in English as The Centipede Party, since Stonoga translates as \"centipede\").<ref>{{cite news| url = http://telewizjarepublika.pl/stonoga-partia-polska-rejestracja-nowej-formacji-politycznej-moze-nastapic-lada-dzien,20590.htm| title = \"Stonoga Partia Polska. Rejestracja nowej formacji politycznej mo\u017ce nast\u0105pi\u0107 lada dzie\u0144\". | date = 10 June 2015 | accessdate  = 18 June 2015 }}</ref> Founder of ''Gazeta Stonoga'' (now defunct). Convicted for financial fraud.\n\n==Biography ==\n\n=== Academic background ===\nAfter graduating from an electrotechnical college, he started higher education which he did not complete. Claims to have studied law at the [[University of Warsaw]]; however, the University denies such person has ever attended the university.<ref name=\"dziennik1\"/>\n\n=== Political career ===\nIn 2015 he ran in Polish parliamentary elections in which his party, Stonoga Party Poland, scored 0.4% (40 000 voters). After the results were announced, furious Stonoga uploaded a video to the internet in which he expressed his frustration with those who did not vote for him or for the [[Coalition for the Renewal of the Republic - Liberty and Hope]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qARYM_ACOk|title=Zbigniew Stonoga obra\u017ca Polak\u00f3w: \"WAS POLACZKI TYLKO DO AUSCHWITZ WYPROWADZI\u0106\"|date=2015-08-31|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=2017-04-20}}</ref>\n\nHis language is vulgar and direct, attracting the attention of young audiences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kontrrewolucja.net/wiadomosci/stonoga-szokuje-wulgarnie-wyzywa-politykow-tym-prezydenta|title=Stonoga znowu szokuje. Wulgarnie wyzywa polityk\u00f3w, w tym prezydenta (WIDEO)|date=2017-04-06|website=Kontrrewolucja.net|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pch24.pl/glupie-polaczki--was-tylko-do-auschwitz-zaprowadzac---sfrustrowany-stonoga-o-porazce-wyborczej--w-kolejnym-nagraniu-przeprosil-za-slowa,39007,i.html|title=\"G\u0142upie polaczki, was tylko do Auschwitz zaprowadza\u0107\" \u2013 sfrustrowany Stonoga o pora\u017cce wyborczej. W kolejnym nagraniu przeprosi\u0142 za s\u0142owa|website=Pch24.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n==  Lawsuits ==\nIn the 2000s Stonoga was named in a total of 89 criminal lawsuits.\n\nIn 2004 he was sentenced to 3.5 years' imprisonment for financial irregularities. In 2005 his sentence was quashed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ju\u017c si\u0119 powyg\u0142upia\u0142em, pokl\u0105\u0142em. Tak wojuje Zbigniew Stonoga. SYLWETKA |url = http://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/wydarzenia/artykuly/475076,zbigniew-stonoga-kontra-sokolowski-i-sld-wojny-zbigniewa-stonogi.html |language=pl| accessdate = 18 June 2015| date = 9 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nBy 2015, he was named in 61 criminal cases related mostly to financial fraud and insulting public servants; he was sentenced to a year in prison for fraud on a private car sale.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.polityka.pl/tygodnikpolityka/kraj/1623573,1,stonoga-raczej-do-wiezienia-niz-do-sejmu.read | title = Stonoga raczej do wi\u0119zienia ni\u017c do Sejmu | language=pl}}</ref>\n\nOn May 9, 2017, Stonoga was imprisoned at the Warszawa-Bialoleka correctional center for one year on charges of committing a large-scale financial fraud; the sentence was later shortened by 3 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wprost.pl/kraj/10053826/zbigniew-stonoga-trafil-do-wiezienia-spedzi-tam-niecaly-rok.html|title=Zbigniew Stonoga trafi\u0142 do wi\u0119zienia. Sp\u0119dzi tam nieca\u0142y rok|date=2017-05-09|website=Wprost|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.wp.pl/zbigniew-stonoga-za-kratkami-spedzi-tam-dluzszy-czas-6120729443526785a|title=Zbigniew Stonoga za kratkami. Sp\u0119dzi tam d\u0142u\u017cszy czas|last=K\u0142oszewski|first=oprac Jakub|date=2017-05-09|website=wiadomosci.wp.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dziennikzachodni.pl/zbigniew-stonoga-wyszedl-z-wiezienia-i-prosi-o-wplate-200-tys-zl-na-wolnosci-opublikowal-wideo-27-9-2019/ar/c1-14433723|title=Zbigniew Stonoga wyszed\u0142 z wi\u0119zienia i prosi o wp\u0142at\u0119 200 tys. z\u0142. Na wolno\u015bci opublikowa\u0142 wideo [27. 9. 2019]|last=Redakcja|date=2019-09-27|website=Dziennik Zachodni|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Wikiquote|Zbigniew Stonoga}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stonoga, Zbigniew}}\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Polish businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Polish activists]]\n[[Category:Polish politicians]]\n[[Category:Polish YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Whistleblowers]]\n[[Category:Men whistleblowers]]\n\n\n{{Poland-business-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Kashmiri", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zbigniew_Stonoga"}
